problem:
This demonstrates the use of the loupeAndLightbox javascript helper to allow detailed exploration of an image.
This is not a problem type pe se, but it may be useful in writing problems.
You can view the chemical structures of the molecules by clicking on them.  The maginfied view will also list the enzymes involved in each step.

        $(function() {
                    $('.loupe').loupeAndLightbox({
                        width:300,
                        height:300,
                        lightbox:false
                        });  });


Here is the code used:

  <div class="place" id="place1" style="position: relative">        
    <a href="/static/images/magnify.png" class="loupe"><img src="/static/images/magnifySmall.png" alt="magnify" /></a>
  </div>
  <script type="text/javascript" src="/static/js/loupeAndLightbox/jquery.loupeAndLightbox.js"></script>
  <script type="text/javascript">
        $(function() {
                    $('.loupe').loupeAndLightbox({
                        width:300,
                        height:300,
                        lightbox:false
                        });  });
  </script>
